There are two ways to push.

1.In the git hub, click add file => upload file.In the coming window, it shows to drag and drop.Minimise the window, drag the file from the system and drop in the github.

2.Using gitbash, to push, first we have to clone the remote repository to the local system.
 > git clone ' url '

 then, that repository will be seen the computer.Copy the file to be uploaded into the new local repository.
 Change the directory to the local repository with the command => cd name

 Now we have to stage the file.
 => git add .

 Then commit
 => git commit -m 'message'

 Then push
 => git push origin main   // The branch can be depending upon the branch selected in the github [master or main]
